by Socialist Communist States » Fri Apr 17, 2020 3:24 pm

The constitution of the Federation is divided into 5 sections. The first section being that their nation can override election and ban people. It also deals with when an election is set and where they will be appointed. The second section mainly just names the position of authority. The third section deals with appointments and scenarios on if a vote fails. The fourth section deals with citizenship, and the 5th section deals with RMB rules. The constitution can be changed by their nation at any time.

The colonial-era of New Spiedeska is similar to that of our timeline, but with Inklings. During this time, the area of what we would call modern day New York State is New Amsterdam. Later on the English would take it off them and develop it as a part of the other 12 colonial territories. Similarly in our timeline, there is a war of independence, which New Spedskia would win in 1783. However, in 1865 a civil war breaks out that lasts for 10 years, which kills 7% of the female population.
